g.title: EleanorRank1Convo3 begins.
g.text: EleanorRank1Convo3 begins.

g.title: j2623024995
g.text: So. The Void.

g.title: j1238905418
g.text: I'm honestly quite curious about it. So...

g.title: j558618700
g.text: ... would it be okay to just fire some questions at you?

g.title: j3114044247
g.text: Sure.

g.title: j1099755940
g.text: I might not have all the answers, but go ahead.

g.title: j3901902390
g.text: No. [End.]

g.title: j4263536219
g.text: Excellent. So...

g.title: j2785516483
g.text: +10 Chemistry

g.title: j4037370335
g.text: ... and thus you retain that aura of cryptic mystery I so admire.

g.title: j2270186134
g.text: … how would you sum up what the Void means to you, in a few words?

g.title: j3327340735
g.text: Your honesty is noted and appreciated.

g.title: Chat ends.
g.text: Chat ends.

g.title: j518248235
g.text: I feel put on the spot. Is this an interview?

g.title: j296001982
g.text: What it “means” to me?

g.title: j2840227955
g.text: Nobody’s really sure what the Void is. It’s a dimension, it’s an energy field, it’s a shortcut through space, it’s a bolt-hole where the Orokin hid…

g.title: j819787031
g.text: Sorry. Old habits.

g.title: j3041875353
g.text: Yes.

g.title: j57471549
g.text: Fascinating though all that is, it sounds technical. I was more interested in what it means to you. Since you seem to, well, live and breathe it. Literally.

g.title: j2790059144
g.text: Forgive me. I’m not a journo any more, and you’re not the story. I’m just deeply interested.

g.title: j411325889
g.text: Get personal with it.

g.title: j2842209284
g.text: The Void gives me the ability to do impossible things. Project beams of energy, turn insubstantial, all that good shit. Where I come from, it’s what makes Warframes able to do what they do.

g.title: j3668070756
g.text: The Void drove my parents insane.

g.title: j1160905911
g.text: The Void was my home for I don’t know how long. It shaped itself to me. Or I shaped it, somehow. Still not clear on what exactly happened.

g.title: j3778343833
g.text: Wait. Wait.

g.title: j1497149933
g.text: I’m sorry. Now I feel like a heel for asking.

g.title: j3633759760
g.text: Ooh. You have my full attention.

g.title: j39260377
g.text: The Void is a miracle engine, is what you’re saying?

g.title: j180836375
g.text: Did they recover?

g.title: j3631955467
g.text: Check boolean EleanorDuviri

g.title: j665088767
g.text: And I’m already connected to it?

g.title: j922550161
g.text: They never had the chance.

g.title: j3043812902
g.text: By shape you mean… Duviri? Towers and islands and flying horses?

g.title: j3631955467->j3043812902
g.text: true

g.title: j1258182388
g.text: What shape did it take?

g.title: j3631955467->j1258182388
g.text: false

g.title: j4230848134
g.text: What do you mean, connected?

g.title: j2428709361
g.text: Oh Sol. That’s horrible.

g.title: j3629285586
g.text: Yeah. Literally a children’s story brought to life.

g.title: j1477545664
g.text: There was this book I used to love. ‘Tales of Duviri’. Stories about a magical kingdom, only it was really about emotions and the lessons they can teach you.

g.title: j321341173
g.text: I mean I’m a Warframe. Or a Protoframe. I’m like them.

g.title: j387802697
g.text: Would you rather not talk about this right now?

g.title: j3207012295
g.text: And this was real? It didn’t feel like a dream?

g.title: j3680300068
g.text: The Void brought it to life and I got to live in it. Then it became a prison. But that’s another story.

g.title: j3018776744
g.text: And I can do things now. Mind control. Face melting.

g.title: j3564990633
g.text: I'm good.

g.title: j3596412113
g.text: Yeah, I'd rather not. [End.]

g.title: j3486930230
g.text: No, Eleanor, being murdered every morning did not feel like a dream. I felt every second of it.

g.title: j201455776
g.text: Boolean EleanorDuviri is now true.

g.title: j1743911248
g.text: Is that where the power’s coming from IN ME? The Void?

g.title: j2495035829
g.text: Separating parents from children. Turning one against the other. That doesn’t sound coincidental to me.

g.title: j1988694573
g.text: Another time, then.

g.title: j2258942123
g.text: I see.

g.title: j839325465
g.text: Wait, back up. In my time, there’s this… pump. The Heart of Deimos.

g.title: j1500488810
g.text: That sounds like conscious intent.

g.title: j575655746
g.text: Boolean EleanorDrifterParentsAsked is now true.

g.title: j4268660167
g.text: I…

g.title: j974634559
g.text: One sec. Getting comfortable.

g.title: j1450480518
g.text: Like twisted science, almost.

g.title: j162008127
g.text: I have to wonder what that’s like.

g.title: j4072857550
g.text: Right. As you were. I can’t wait to hear this.

g.title: j2694926244
g.text: Yeah. There’s something IN the Void. I know that much. The Indifference, the Lidless Eye, the ‘Man in the Wall’. When I say the Void did this, I mean HE did it.

g.title: j1211060761
g.text: Words, brought to life. A concrete reality, conjured out of nothing.

g.title: j3445635724
g.text: The Heart of Deimos keeps the whole Origin System bathed in a sort of Void halo. Like background radiation. Anything that draws on Void energy depends on the Heart.

g.title: j1797633318
g.text: So they’re not one and the same thing?

g.title: j4180940185
g.text: ‘Magic’ seems too small a word for it.

g.title: j4058537749
g.text: Well now.

g.title: j1064317005
g.text: They could be. I hope they aren’t.

g.title: j1461728333
g.text: +10 Chemistry

g.title: j3580448643
g.text: If there’s no Heart of Deimos in my time, then how is the Void reaching me?

g.title: j2614067758
g.text: Boolean EleanorDrifterParents is now true.

g.title: j3666629503
g.text: What you’re describing is divine.

g.title: j3396125770
g.text: Because I can feel it, you know. I’m sure I can.

g.title: j4165792530
g.text: Fascinating.

g.title: j3036352955
g.text: Boolean EleanorVoidLove is now true.

g.title: j3353511665
g.text: And why is that?

g.title: j2158955028
g.text: The future basically RUNS on the Void. Interplanetary travel, Warframes, the Tenno... without the Void, none of it works.
